ENVO has a broad temperate classification, but not finer grained classes suitable for matching against the WTE cool and warm temperate temperature domains.  Also note, the ENVO classification of temperate is not based on temperature per se, rather, it is a relative classification between two qualitative bounds.

Also note, the ENVO classification of temperate is not based on temperature per se, rather, it is a relative classification between two qualitative bounds.
ENVO's subtropical classification does not have same temperature range as WTE however, the relative positioning of ENVO subtropical between tropical and temperate is congruent with WTE.
ENVO's tropical classification does not have same temperature range as WTE however, the relative positioning of ENVO tropical, with respect to subtropical, is congruent with WTE.

ENVO's humid air classification does not define an aridity index value and therefore does not form an exact match with WTE however, the qualitative attributes of WTE moist and ENVO humid air do match.
ENVO's arid classification has slightly different quantitative definition than WTE Dry and is therefore not an exact match.
ENVO does not have a hyperarid classification that matches WTE Desert. ENVO's desert area forms a close lexical match but is more related to ENVO arid than to WTE desert.
